	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I am a 15th level Dark Elf SK who makes a good living killing bears for HQ pelts and Wisps for GLS.  I can make 100PP in 2 or 3 hours (luck plays a factor) hunting just these two creture types in the Commons and Nek Forest.<BR>
<BR>
I've killed hundreds of bears, and the secret to getting an HQ pelt is speed.  The faster you kill the bear the better the chance you'll score an HQ pelt.  I can kill a Black Bear in three hits with my BBC, and routinely get a HQ pelt every 20 Black Bears or so.  HQ pelts can also be obtained from YKs, Kodiaks, and other bear types, but obviously the more HP the bear has the longer it will take you to kill it, and the lower your chances of obtaining an HQ pelt will be.  Cat pelts work the same way, but there is a much lower market for them (I think tailors can make armor from cat pelts where as bear pelts are made into 50PP 10-slot Backpacks)<BR>
<BR>
You're getting ripped off if you accept less than 12PP for an HQ Bear Pelt.  Many tailors with high success rates on backpacks will give you 15-20PP per pelt.  Obviously you should work out a deal to trade your first couple of pelts and a few plat for a couple of 10-slot packs for yourself, as they're handy to have! =)<BR>
<BR>
Raveneye<BR>

